      <hedline>
        <hl1>Cheating Shoppers</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I hope the sudden death of the WebHouse service for groceries and gasoline hasn't made Michelle Slatalla feel guilty (Online Shopper, ''Making a Dent in the Price of Gas,'' Oct. 5, and ''Confessions of an Online Applesauce Thief,'' April 13). I don't buy Priceline's statement that only 1 percent of WebHouse's customers cheated. Everyone I know did. But then again, I live in Brooklyn.</p>
        <p>VIKTOR FROLKE  Brooklyn</p>
      </block>
